description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Give your career a positive change.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cygnet Hospital Bierley provides a range of low secure, specialist and psychiatric intensive care services for men and women, including a specialist personality disorder service for women.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an exciting opportunity to pilot a small team of dedicated, passionate and resilient staff to work directly with a female service user who has complex behaviours, aggression and suffers with a complex eating disorder.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an opportunity to work as part of a highly specialised commissioned team. This role will build on the successful applicant’s skills to become specialised in personality disorders and eating difficulties.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This position is working both days and nights. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;In this role you’ll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work as part of a specialised team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively with the clinical team leader or Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote an environment of co-production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Function as a competent member of the team in any situation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report accidents and untoward incidents to patients, visitors or staff, to the Clinical Team Leader&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend review meetings as directed on the ward and in the Hospital&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive supervision from registered nurses and attend support groups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to ward audits and action plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aware of safeguarding requirements and the need to report issues to Clinical team Leader&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development and review of ward manual and philosophy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Abide by guidelines and hospital policies and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for people who have:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Minimum of 1 years’ experience in Mental Health Services Preferably on Acute, PD Services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience supporting service users with Challenging behaviours including violence and aggression.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work in a faced paced changing environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Genuine desire to make a real difference in people’s lives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills and the ability to work as a good team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Sensitive and intuitive energy required to provide a trusting, stimulating &amp; varied environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Why Cygnet? We’ll offer you…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Group Pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Staff Discounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhanced Maternity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Health Cash Plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Referral Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;24 Hours Free GP Helpline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounted Gym Membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cycle To Work Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On-site Benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Mortgage Broker &amp; Insurance Cover&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Assistance Programme (EAP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Eye Tests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Car Lease Discounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Life Assurance Company scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smart Health Toolkit- Providing you with Fitness Programmes, Nutrition consultation and Health checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ready to make a positive change? Please click on the ‘apply now’ link below&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Join us!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
